{"legislative_session": "153", "identifier": "HB 15", "title": "AN ACT TO AMEND TITLE 14 OF THE DELAWARE CODE RELATING TO PLAY-BASED LEARNING IN EARLY CHILDHOOD EDUCATION.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": [], "abstracts": [{"note": "synopsis", "abstract": "Like House Bill No. 15, this Act permits early childhood educators in the public schools to use and encourage play-based learning in their classrooms and in their curriculum. This Act permits local education agencies to provide early childhood professional development in play-based learning, which may include professional development programs developed by the Department of Education. This Act also permits the Department to promulgate regulations for purposes of implementing this Act.\r\nThis House Substitute No. 1 for House Bill No. 15 incorporates the changes from House Amendment 1 to House Bill No. 15 with respect to the definitions of early childhood education and early childhood educators encompassing education from prekindergarten through second grade, adding topics that may be included in materials developed to provide ongoing early childhood professional development in play-based learning, and making technical corrections for clarity.\r\nThis House Substitute also updates the definition of \u201cplay\u201d and \u201cplay-based learning\u201d contained in House Bill No. 15 and adds a definition for \u201cguided play\u201d."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "short title", "title": "Play-Based Learning/Encourage/Public Schools"}], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "was introduced and adopted in lieu of HB 15", "date": "2025-04-03", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["introduction"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Passed By House. Votes: 38 YES 3 ABSENT", "date": "2025-06-12", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["passage"], "related_entities": []